  "AIA:sandy hill bay": "A tranquil, undeveloped bay on Anguilla's southeastern coast used as a protected anchorage for fishing boats, with no hotels or restaurants.",
  "AIA:island harbour": "A traditional fishing village on the northeast coast, host of the annual Festival del Mar each Easter weekend celebrating boat racing and seafood.",
  "AIA:george hill": "A central residential district notable for the Anguilla Arch, a dramatic natural coastal rock formation with panoramic Caribbean Sea views.",
  "AIA:the quarter": "A district adjacent to The Valley that contains Clayton J. Lloyd International Airport (AXA), Anguilla's sole commercial airport.",
  // ALB
