  "IRN:kermanshah": "Home to the Bisotun UNESCO World Heritage Site, featuring Darius the Great's trilingual rock inscription from the 5th century BC.",
  "IRN:ilam": "Westernmost province bordering Iraq, known for its Zagros mountain scenery, ancient Elamite ruins, and natural gas reserves.",
  "IRN:khuzestan": "Iran's oil heartland, producing the majority of the country's petroleum output, with the ancient Elamite city of Susa (Shush) within its borders.",
