  "IRQ:saladin": "Contains Samarra's iconic spiral-minaret Al-Askari Shrine and the ruins of the ancient Abbasid capital of Samarra, a UNESCO site.",
  "IRQ:kirkuk": "Sits atop one of the world's largest oil fields; its status is disputed between the Iraqi federal government and Kurdistan Region.",
  "IRQ:baghdad": "Iraq's capital province and most populous; the city of Baghdad was founded in 762 CE as the Abbasid Caliphate's round city.",
  "IRQ:babylon": "Home to the ruins of ancient Babylon, including Nebuchadnezzar II's palace complex, designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2019.",
  "IRQ:al-qādisiyyah": "Named after the 636 CE Battle of al-Qadisiyyah where Arab Muslim forces defeated the Sassanid Persian Empire; capital is Ad-Diwaniyah.",
