  "UGA:buyende": "A Busoga district bordered by Lake Kyoga, with an economy dominated by fishing and cassava cultivation.",
  "UGA:jinja": "Located at the source of the Nile from Lake Victoria, historically Uganda's industrial capital and a whitewater rafting hub.",
  "UGA:apac": "A Lango region district on the shore of Lake Kwania, known for cotton production and fishing on Lake Kyoga.",
  "UGA:nakasongola": "Known for cattle ranching on semi-arid plains and the Nakasongola Military Airfield in central Uganda.",
